19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 29 O.S. 2021, Section 4-114, as
21 amended by Section 6, Chapter 6, O.S.L. 2024 (29 O.S. Supp. 2024,
22 Section 4-114), is amended to read as follows:
23 Section 4-114. A. All legal residents who have resided in the
24 state for at least six (6) months and intend to remain residents,
Req. No. 12937 Page 1
1 and nonresidents pursuant to the requirements provided in subsection
2 J of this section, may purchase lifetime fishing licenses or
3 lifetime combination hunting and fishing licenses from the State
4 Wildlife Conservation Director.
5 B. The fee for these licenses for legal residents shall be:
6 1. Lifetime fishing license, Three Hundred Seventy-five Dollars
7 ($375.00);
8 2. Lifetime combination hunting and fishing license, One
9 Thousand Twenty-four Dollars ($1,024.00);
10 3. Senior citizen lifetime fishing license for persons sixty-
11 five (65) years of age or older, Thirty Dollars ($30.00); and
12 4. Senior citizen lifetime combination hunting and fishing
13 license for persons sixty-five (65) years of age or older, Sixty
14 Dollars ($60.00).
15 C. Legal The fee for these licenses for nonresidents shall be:
16 1. Lifetime fishing license, Three Thousand Dollars
17 ($3,000.00);
18 2. Lifetime combination hunting and fishing license, Seven
19 Thousand Five Hundred Dollars ($7,500.00);
20 3. Senior citizen lifetime fishing license for persons sixty-
21 five (65) years of age or older, Two Hundred Dollars ($200.00); and
22 4. Senior citizen lifetime combination hunting and fishing
23 license for persons sixty-five (65) years of age or older, Four
24 Hundred Dollars ($400.00).
Req. No. 12937 Page 2
1 D. A resident having proper certification from the United
2 States Department of Veterans Affairs or its successor certifying
3 that the person is a disabled veteran and registered with the
4 veterans registry created by the Oklahoma Department of Veterans
5 Affairs may purchase a disability lifetime combination hunting and
6 fishing license from the State Wildlife Conservation Director. The
7 fees for the license shall be as follows:
8 1. Two Hundred Dollars ($200.00) for veterans having a
9 disability of less than sixty percent (60%); and
10 2. Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00) for veterans having a
11 disability of sixty percent (60%) or more.
12 D. E. The use of the licenses provided in this section are
13 subject to those restrictions provided by statute and the
14 regulations of the Wildlife Conservation Commission. Except as
15 otherwise provided for in this section, each lifetime hunting
16 license issued pursuant to subsections B and, C, and D of this
17 section shall be in lieu of all annual hunting licenses and all
18 special season permits.
19 E. F. Should any lifetime license be lost or destroyed, a
20 duplicate will be issued by the Department of Wildlife Conservation
21 for a fee not more than Ten Dollars ($10.00).
22 F. G. A lifetime licensee shall not lose the privileges of such
23 license by a subsequent transfer of residency.
24
Req. No. 12937 Page 3
1 G. H. A person who is sixty-four (64) years of age shall be
2 eligible to purchase a senior citizen lifetime license issued
3 pursuant to paragraphs 4 through 6 of subsection subsections B and C
4 of this section during the calendar year in which the person turns
5 sixty-five (65) years of age.
6 H. I. The Oklahoma Wildlife Conservation Commission shall
7 promulgate any rules necessary to implement the provisions of this
8 section.
9 J. The licenses for a nonresident under this section shall be
10 issued to any nonresident, which shall include the spouse and
11 children, who are under eighteen (18) years of age, of the
12 nonresident, who hunts on land he or she owns that:
13 1. Is a minimum of one hundred sixty (160) acres;
14 2. Is not owned by a trust, any type of business entity, or by
15 multiple owners, excluding joint tenants with the right of
16 survivorship;
17 3. Has been owned by the nonresident for at least one (1) year;
18 4. The nonresident has paid property taxes on the land for the
19 previous year; and
20 5. The nonresident has shown proof of both ownership and paid
21 taxes to the Oklahoma Department of Wildlife Conservation.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
23 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
Req. No. 12937 Page 4
1 decl ared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
2 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
